<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,1531]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,342,576,602]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Comments:</emphasis>
Epilithic thalli were found attached to the substrate and were collected from tide pools exposed to wave action or on sand, partially submersed or from the frontal area of sandstone reefs (CE, BA, 
<collectionCode box="[151,191,654,680]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">ES</collectionCode>
). The species grows close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1849" box="[565,772,655,680]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="montagneana">
<emphasis box="[565,772,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. montagneana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1843" baseAuthorityName="Roth" box="[790,938,655,680]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="prolifera">
<emphasis box="[790,938,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. prolifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[957,1132,655,680]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="vagabunda">
<emphasis box="[957,1132,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. vagabunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1150,1352,654,680]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Ceramiaceae" genus="Centroceras" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ceramiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1150,1303,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Centroceras</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamouroux" authorityYear="1816" family="Corallinaceae" genus="Jania" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cryptonemiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="adhaerens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Jania adhaerens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[348,700,693,718]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Chondracanthidae" genus="Chondracanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilostomatoida" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acicularis">
<emphasis box="[348,700,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Chondracanthus acicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The thalli of 
<taxonomicName box="[892,1040,693,718]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Willeella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[892,1040,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the following epiphytes: 
<taxonomicName authority="Kutzing (1843 b: 385)" authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1843" box="[151,672,732,758]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Corallinaceae" genus="Pneophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Corallinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="fragile">
<emphasis box="[151,398,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Pneophyllum fragile</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kutzing, F. T." box="[407,672,732,758]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" pagination="75 - 107" refId="ref14619" refString="Kutzing, F. T. (1843 b) Uber die systematische Eintheilung der Algen. Linnea 17: 75 - 107." type="journal article" year="1843">Kützing (1843b: 385)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva et al (1987: 56)" authorityName="Silva" authorityYear="1987" box="[686,1178,732,758]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Ceramiaceae" genus="Ceramium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ceramiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis box="[686,907,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Ceramium vagans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, P. C. &amp; Menez, E. G. &amp; Moe, R. L." box="[915,1178,732,758]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 179" refId="ref16415" refString="Silva, P. C., Menez, E. G. &amp; Moe, R. L. (1987) Catalog of the benthic marine algae of the Philippines. Smithsonian Contributions to Marine Sciences 27: 1 - 179." type="journal article" year="1987">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[986,1039,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
(1987: 56)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, benthic diatoms and cyanobacteria.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,1531]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">
Along the Brazilian coast, 
<taxonomicName box="[519,655,809,834]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Willeella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[519,655,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs from 
<collectingRegion box="[815,883,809,835]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Ceará</collectingRegion>
to the south of 
<collectingRegion box="[1076,1247,809,835]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, confirming the tropical distribution of this species. Cell dimensions were very similar in specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[1230,1302,848,874]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Ceará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1315,1384,848,874]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,322,886,912]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,1531]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[198,453,925,950]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[198,453,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Cladophora ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most characteristic species of the genus due to its ramification pattern. Therefore, there are no difficulties in identifying this species. Previously, 
<taxonomicName box="[1019,1123,964,989]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Willeella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1019,1123,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Willeella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered a separate genus from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kutzing" authorityYear="1843" box="[292,434,1002,1027]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[292,434,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Cladophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoek, C. van den" box="[495,644,1002,1028]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" refId="ref13956" refString="Hoek, C. van den (1982) A taxonomic revision of the American species of Cladophora (Chlorophyceae) in the North Atlantic Ocean and their geographic distribution. North-Holland Publishing Company, Amsterdam, 236 pp." type="book" year="1982">Hoek (1982)</bibRefCitation>
argued that the characteristics that distinguished it from its closely related species (
<taxonomicName box="[340,497,1041,1066]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="jongiorum">
<emphasis box="[340,497,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. jongiorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuetzing" authorityYear="1843" baseAuthorityName="Hudson" box="[512,632,1041,1066]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis box="[512,632,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuetzing" authorityYear="1843" baseAuthorityName="Nees Kuetzing" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[689,799,1041,1066]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis box="[689,799,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. albida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were insufficient to consider it a separate genus. The specimens studied match descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[654,794,1080,1105]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[654,794,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the American North Atlantic (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoek, C. van den" box="[1237,1375,1080,1106]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" refId="ref13956" refString="Hoek, C. van den (1982) A taxonomic revision of the American species of Cladophora (Chlorophyceae) in the North Atlantic Ocean and their geographic distribution. North-Holland Publishing Company, Amsterdam, 236 pp." type="book" year="1982">Hoek 1982</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,1118,1144]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Hoek &amp; Chirara 2000). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoek, C. van den &amp; Chihara, M." box="[683,968,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" refId="ref13996" refString="Hoek, C. van den &amp; Chihara, M. (2000) A taxonomic revision of the marine species of Cladophora (Chlorophyta) along the coasts of Japan and Russian Far-East. National Science Museum, Tokyo, 242 pp." type="book" year="2000">Hoek &amp; Chihara (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[981,1117,1119,1144]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[981,1117,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a sub-tidal species from the open sea and is only collected from deep water. However, in 
<collectingCountry box="[929,1051,1157,1183]" name="Venezuela" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[1060,1196,1157,1182]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[1060,1196,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found growing attached to stones in areas of moderate wave action and approximately 
<quantity box="[984,1058,1195,1222]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">
1 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[999,1014,1195,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">–</emphasis>
2 m
</quantity>
in depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoek, C. van den" box="[1175,1311,1196,1222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" refId="ref13956" refString="Hoek, C. van den (1982) A taxonomic revision of the American species of Cladophora (Chlorophyceae) in the North Atlantic Ocean and their geographic distribution. North-Holland Publishing Company, Amsterdam, 236 pp." type="book" year="1982">Hoek 1982</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1362,1431,1196,1222]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[151,285,1235,1260]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[151,285,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs on sandy bottoms, pebbles, stones and on crustose coralline algae in water that is 
<quantity box="[1332,1436,1234,1260]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="27.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="25.0">
25 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1362,1377,1234,1260]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">–</emphasis>
30 m
</quantity>
deep. Off the west coast of Africa, specimens (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[780,923,1273,1298]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[780,923,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">W. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were collected from water 
<quantity box="[1276,1370,1272,1299]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="11.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="8.0">
8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1292,1307,1272,1298]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">–</emphasis>
14 m
</quantity>
deep (
<bibRefCitation author="Lawson, G. W. &amp; John, D. M." box="[159,422,1312,1338]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 455" refId="ref15032" refString="Lawson, G. W. &amp; John, D. M. (1982) The marine algae and coastal environment of tropical West Africa. Nova Hedwigia 70: 1 - 455." type="journal article" year="1982">Lawson &amp; John 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoneshigue-Valentin, Y. &amp; Gestinari, L. M. S. &amp; Fernandes, D. R. P." box="[562,964,1312,1338]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" pagination="67 - 105" refId="ref16970" refString="Yoneshigue-Valentin, Y., Gestinari, L. M. S. &amp; Fernandes, D. R. P. (2006) Macroalgas. In: Lavrado, H. P. &amp; Ignacio, B. L. (Eds), Biodiversidade bentonica da regiao central da Zona Economica Exclusiva brasileira. Museu Nacional, Rio de Janeiro,. pp. 67 - 105." type="book chapter" year="2006">
Yoneshigue-Valentin 
<emphasis box="[817,877,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[1300,1436,1312,1337]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[1300,1436,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">C. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[197,344,1351,1376]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[197,344,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">W. ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in deep water (
<quantity box="[556,624,1350,1376]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="58.0">58 m</quantity>
) off the south coast of Bahia (
<geoCoordinate box="[1017,1171,1350,1376]" degrees="16" direction="south" minutes="47" orientation="latitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" precision="15" seconds="14" value="-16.787222">16°47’14’’S</geoCoordinate>
and 
<geoCoordinate box="[1236,1422,1350,1376]" degrees="038" direction="west" minutes="41" orientation="longitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" precision="15" seconds="33" value="-38.6925">038°41’33’’W</geoCoordinate>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Bfrgesen" box="[151,400,1389,1414]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="ordinata">
<emphasis box="[151,400,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Cladophora ordinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the tropical amphiatlantic group and has been collected in the Caribbean, the tropical Indian Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, P. C. &amp; Basson, P. W. &amp; Moe, R. L." box="[423,622,1428,1454]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" refId="ref16459" refString="Silva, P. C., Basson, P. W. &amp; Moe, R. L. (1996) Catalogue of the marine algae of the Indian Ocean. University of California Press, Berkeley, 1259 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[492,552,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<collectingCountry box="[694,764,1428,1454]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Japan</collectingCountry>
, its northern limit (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoek, C. van den &amp; Chihara, M." box="[991,1260,1428,1454]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32" refId="ref13996" refString="Hoek, C. van den &amp; Chihara, M. (2000) A taxonomic revision of the marine species of Cladophora (Chlorophyta) along the coasts of Japan and Russian Far-East. National Science Museum, Tokyo, 242 pp." type="book" year="2000">Hoek &amp; Chihara 2000</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1313,1388,1428,1454]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, the boundary of its distribution is the south of 
<collectingRegion box="[661,833,1466,1492]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
. This study presents the first record of this species from 
<collectingRegion box="[215,287,1505,1531]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Ceará</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
